Re: Source code documentation

Bitcointalk

2010-07-16 15:37:00 UTC - [11]Original Post

   I like that in libraries for the external APIʼs, but you can probably
   tell from the code that Iʼm not a fan of it for interior functions.
   Big obligatory comment headers for each function space out the code and
   make you hesitate about creating a small little function where the
   comment header would be bigger than the function.  Theyʼre some trouble
   for maintenance, as changes to the function then require duplicate
   changes in the comment header.  I like to keep code compact so you can
   see more code on the screen at once.
   To add them now at this point, what would be written would just be
   whatʼs obvious from looking at the function.
   The external API we have, in rpc.cpp, the usage documentation is in the
   help string.
   Sorry to be a wet blanket.
